Question:
Let S be the set of all real values of $$\lambda $$ such that a plane passing through the points (–$$\lambda $$<sup>2</sup>, 1, 1), (1, –$$\lambda $$<sup>2</sup>, 1) and (1, 1, – $$\lambda $$<sup>2</sup>) also passes through the point (–1, –1, 1). Then S is equal to :

Options:
A: {1, $$-$$1}
B: {3, $$-$$ 3}
C: $$\left\{ {\sqrt 3 } \right\}$$
D: $$\left\{ {\sqrt 3 , - \sqrt 3 } \right\}$$
